summary: JON SNOW WEEK | Day One Favorite Season › Season Six  If it weren’t for him, none of us would be here. All of you would be meat...
caption:
JON SNOW WEEK | Day One
Favorite Season › Season Six

If it weren’t for him, none of us would be here. All of you would be meat in the Night King’s army. And I’d be a pile of charred bones just like Mance. The crows killed him because he spoke for the free folk when no other southerners would. He died for us. If we are not willing to do the same for him, we’re cowards. And if that’s what we are, we deserve to be the last of the free folk.

summary: This claim that Jonsas are making up romantic tension/chemistry with Jon and Sansa is silly. Are we going to pretend that during...
body: This claim that Jonsas are making up romantic tension/chemistry with Jon and Sansa is silly. Are we going to pretend that during and after season 6, Twitter and the media didn’t blow up with Jonsa speculation? It seemed like most of the general audience and the media picked up on some sexual tension between the pair. So does that mean that most of us are just delusional and are seeing things that are not there? I highly doubt it. Also this idea that the majority of people are rooting for Jon and Dany as a couple is simply not true. After the finale aired most of the general audience had mixed feelings about the pair especially after the cringey boatsex scene.

summary: I didn't notice this before but when the camera is on Sansa after the knights of the vale defeat Ramsay's army, the Stark theme...
body: I didn’t notice this before but when the camera is on Sansa after the knights of the vale defeat Ramsay’s army, the Stark theme song is being sung by a woman (or at least in a very high pitched tone) something that has never been done before, which means they especially made that version of the song for Sansa.
